                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14439349" author="bentmann" created="Sat, 14 Nov 2009 07:53:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I guess that the same issue already reported as &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mail-archive.com/dev@maven.apache.org/msg82576.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Regression with maven-javadoc-plugin 2.6.1 and release:perform&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439372" author="henryju" created="Sat, 14 Nov 2009 08:16:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree I think this is the same issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439405" author="bentmann" created="Sat, 14 Nov 2009 08:36:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is in particular problematic as not even &quot;mvn install&quot; makes it work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439381" author="beemsoft" created="Mon, 25 Jan 2010 11:04:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I had a similar issue, while running: mvn site.&lt;br/&gt;
After explicitly running: mvn javadoc:javadoc, this issue didn&apos;t occur any more.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439440" author="shinsato" created="Thu, 18 Mar 2010 08:14:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is happening for us only during release:perform - is there any workaround? It&apos;s confusing why the javadoc for one project gets invoked from another project.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439353" author="fbrier" created="Wed, 21 Apr 2010 03:39:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe I was having this issue with version 2.6.1/Maven 2.2.1.  If I comment out the plugin, it builds fine.  Otherwise, the preceding sibling dependency is &quot;missing&quot;.  I just checked out/built/installed the 2.7-SNAPSHOT and the error is still occurring.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14438538" author="mehtad@hotmail.com" created="Wed, 7 Jul 2010 11:55:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I still see this error with v2.7. What are the configurations to run the plugin in aggreagte mode for a multi-module project?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439488" author="fazend" created="Wed, 13 Oct 2010 09:22:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is still not fixed. Why the issue is closed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439480" author="dantran" created="Sat, 5 Feb 2011 21:33:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;reopen since javadoc plugin 2.7 still see the same issue&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439429" author="jdcasey" created="Mon, 21 Mar 2011 17:21:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;what about 2.8? can we close this issue now that &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-284&quot; title=&quot;detectOfflineLinks sets off extra spurious executions of javadoc&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MJAVADOC-284&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MJAVADOC-284&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is closed? I haven&apos;t seen it, unless you&apos;re talking about the case where the javadoc plugin forks a new build in order to produce javadocs for dependencies...for which there is a flag to skip that, and I&apos;m assuming &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-284&quot; title=&quot;detectOfflineLinks sets off extra spurious executions of javadoc&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MJAVADOC-284&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MJAVADOC-284&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has fixed in a more permanent way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14439360" author="hboutemy" created="Mon, 25 Apr 2011 03:14:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-284&quot; title=&quot;detectOfflineLinks sets off extra spurious executions of javadoc&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MJAVADOC-284&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MJAVADOC-284&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixed, this issue is a duplicate IMHO&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17957508" author="olamy" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2025 03:32:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-javadoc-plugin/issues/574&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-javadoc-plugin#574&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
